div.p:
b) The Camp David Accords created the impression that in fact a separate peace
                    between Egypt and Israel was acceptable to both the US and to Egypt—and for a
                    while I even thought that perhaps you and Sadat had secretly agreed on this;

c) Begin probably does not want to move on
                    the West Bank part of the Accords, and he might be genuinely intimated by his
                    domestic opposition (though he is also doubtlessly exploiting it);
